  "local_port": 41742,
  "remote_port": 443,
  "prompt": "Why can't I change my profile picture on Quora via my phone?",
  "response": "If you're having trouble changing your profile picture on Quora via your phone, there could be several reasons for this issue. Here are some common causes and potential solutions:\n\n### 1. **App Version**\n   - **Issue**: You might be using an outdated version of the Quora app.\n   - **Solution**: Update the Quora app to the latest version available in your app store (Google Play Store for Android or Apple App Store for iOS).\n\n### 2. **App Glitch**\n   - **Issue**: Temporary glitches in the app can prevent certain features from working correctly.\n   - **Solution**: Close the app completely and reopen it, or restart your phone to clear any temporary issues.\n\n### 3. **Browser Issues (if using the mobile website)**\n   - **Issue**: If you're trying to change your profile picture through the Quora mobile website, your browser might be causing the issue.\n   - **Solution**: Try clearing your browser\u2019s cache and cookies, or use a different browser. Alternatively, use the Quora app instead of the mobile website.\n\n### 4. **Permissions**\n   - **Issue**: The app might not have the necessary permissions to access your photos or camera.\n   - **Solution**: Go to your phone\u2019s settings, find the Quora app, and ensure that it has permission to access your photos, camera, and storage.\n\n### 5. **Network Issues**\n   - **Issue**: A weak or unstable internet connection can prevent changes from being saved.\n   - **Solution**: Check your internet connection. Switch to a stronger Wi-Fi or mobile data connection if necessary.\n\n### 6. **Quora Server Issues**\n   - **Issue**: Quora\u2019s servers might be experiencing temporary issues.\n   - **Solution**: Wait for a while and try again later. You can check Quora\u2019s status on social media or websites like Downdetector to see if others are experiencing similar issues.\n\n### 7. **Account Issues**\n   - **Issue**: There might be a problem with your Quora account.\n   - **Solution**: Log out of your Quora account, then log back in. If the issue persists, contact Quora support for assistance.\n\n### 8. **Image Requirements**\n   - **Issue**: The image you\u2019re trying to upload might not meet Quora\u2019s requirements.\n   - **Solution**: Ensure that the image is in a supported format (e.g., JPG, PNG) and within the file size limit. Also, make sure the image is appropriately cropped and meets Quora\u2019s guidelines.\n\n### 9. **Cache and Data**\n   - **Issue**: Corrupted cache or data in the app can cause functionality issues.\n   - **Solution**: Clear the cache and data for the Quora app in your phone\u2019s settings. Note that clearing data will log you out of the app, so make sure you know your login credentials.\n\n### 10. **Device Compatibility**\n   - **Issue**: Your phone\u2019s operating system or hardware might not be fully compatible with the latest version of the Quora app.\n   - **Solution**: Check if your phone\u2019s operating system is up to date. If your phone is too old, you might need to use a different device to make the change.\n\nIf none of these solutions work, consider reaching out to Quora\u2019s support team for further assistance. They can provide more specific guidance based on your account and device.",
  "temperature": 1.0,
